<br>
My guild went up there last night with a few friends. With chain drops as slow as they are in ToV we felt that perhaps we could get some armor for the Rogues and Shamen.<br>
<br>
In 6 hours of cleraring we got 5 drops. Two were Beast Master drops (none on raid), 1 'chanter bracer that the 46 chanter didn't even want, 1 Monk hat that was left to rot (we had 4 monks 53-60) and a Cleric crown that a high 40s guest (not even in full EM yet) looted.<br>
<br>
We did get a fair number of gems, each cleric went home laden with trinkets and about a dozen spells (half of which may be useful).<br>
<br>
There is risk in this zone but I fail to see the reward.<br>
<br>
Yes PoG is cleared regularly by the &quot;Ubers&quot; but that is ONLY to get to Tunare. IF they get any drops they most probably let it rot or give it to their #5 twinks.<br>
<br>
If VI/Sony wants this zone used for anything other than a stageing ground to get to Tunare they need to up the drop rate just a little bit. <p>Runehammer Trollsbane<BR>
Assassin of Cazik-Thule<BR>
<BR>
Runesword<BR>
Shadowblade of Gawain<BR>
"I yam what I yam."<BR>
